  "local_port": 39798,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best digital marketing course online for a beginner?",
  "response": "Choosing the best digital marketing course online for a beginner depends on your learning style, budget, and goals. Here are some highly-rated options that cater to beginners:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Google Digital Garage: Fundamentals of Digital Marketing**\n   - **Why it's great**: Free, beginner-friendly, and created by Google. Covers the basics of SEO, social media, analytics, and more.\n   - **Certification**: Yes (free).\n   - **Duration**: ~40 hours (self-paced).\n   - **Platform**: [Google Digital Garage](https://learndigital.withgoogle.com/digitalgarage)\n\n---\n\n### **2. HubSpot Academy: Digital Marketing Course**\n   - **Why it's great**: Free, comprehensive, and beginner-friendly. Focuses on inbound marketing, content creation, and social media.\n   - **Certification**: Yes (free).\n   - **Duration**: ~5.5 hours (self-paced).\n   - **Platform**: [HubSpot Academy](https://academy.hubspot.com/)\n\n---\n\n### **3. Coursera: Digital Marketing Specialization by the University of Illinois**\n   - **Why it's great**: Beginner-friendly, taught by industry experts, and covers SEO, social media, analytics, and strategy.\n   - **Certification**: Yes (paid).\n   - **Duration**: ~8 months at 3 hours/week (self-paced).\n   - **Platform**: [Coursera](https://www.coursera.org/specializations/digital-marketing)\n\n---\n\n### **4. Udemy: The Complete Digital Marketing Course by Rob Percival and Daragh Walsh**\n   - **Why it's great**: Affordable, beginner-friendly, and covers all aspects of digital marketing, including Facebook Ads, SEO, and email marketing.\n   - **Certification**: Yes (paid).\n   - **Duration**: ~22 hours (self-paced).\n   - **Platform**: [Udemy](https://www.udemy.com)\n\n---\n\n### **5. edX: Professional Certificate in Digital Marketing by BU Questrom School of Business**\n   - **Why it's great**: Beginner-friendly, university-backed, and focuses on strategy, analytics, and social media.\n   - **Certification**: Yes (paid).\n   - **Duration**: ~8 weeks at 6\u20138 hours/week (self-paced).\n   - **Platfform**: [edX](https://www.edx.org/)\n\n---\n\n### **6. Skillshare: Digital Marketing Basics by Brad Merrill**\n   - **Why it's great**: Beginner-friendly, affordable, and focuses on practical skills like social media, email marketing, and analytics.\n   - **Certification**: No.\n   - **Duration**: ~1.5 hours (self-paced).\n   - **Platform**: [Skillshare](https://www.skillshare.com)\n\n---\n\n### **7. Simplilearn: Digital Marketing Certified Associate (DMCA)**\n   - **Why it's great**: Beginner-friendly, comprehensive, and covers SEO, social media, PPC, and analytics.\n   - **Certification**: Yes (paid).\n   - **Duration**: ~4\u20135 weeks (self-paced or live classes).\n   - **Platform**: [Simplilearn](https://www.simplilearn.com)\n\n---\n\n### **Tips for Choosing:**\n1. **Free vs Paid**: Start with free courses (like Google Digital Garage or HubSpot) to gauge your interest before investing in paid courses.\n2. **Certification**: If you need a certificate for your resume, opt for courses that offer one.\n3. **Hands-on Experience**: Look for courses that include practical exercises or projects.\n4. **Platform Reputation**: Choose platforms that are well-known and have good reviews.\n\nLet me know if you'd like more help!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
